### Yellow Paper Templates

- **Helper Doc Template** (create in `yellowpaper/helpers/<section>-helper.md`):

```
# <Section Name> — Helper Doc

Purpose: <1-2 sentences>
Scope: <what is in/out>
Dependencies: <related sections/terms>

Key Definitions:
- Term A — definition
- Term B — definition

Key Claims (with sources):
1) <claim> [REF-###]
2) <claim> [REF-###]

Comparative Context:
- <short bullets contrasting alternatives>

Proposed Figures/Tables:
- Figure: <title and what it shows>
- Table: <columns and rationale>

Assumptions & Constraints:
- <assumption>

References:
- [REF-###] <citation>
```

- **Section Draft Template** (create in `yellowpaper/sections/<section>.md`):

```
# <Section Title>

Purpose
- <brief purpose>

Scope
- <in/out of scope>

Dependencies
- <links to related sections>

Content
1. <subtopic heading>
   - <concise explanation at level-200>
   - <cross-references and citations>

Figures
- Figure N: <caption> (see `yellowpaper/figures/fig-N-slug.png`)

Key Takeaways
- <bulleted summary>
```

- **References File Template** (create/update `yellowpaper/context/references.md`):

```
# References

- [REF-001] Author, Title, Year, URL
- [REF-002] Standard/Spec, Title, Organization, Year, URL
```

- **Glossary File Template** (create/update `yellowpaper/context/glossary.md`):

```
# Glossary

- CanonicalTerm: <short definition and role>
```

